description: Sleep, little sprout. Let the dreamtime of the womb cleanse away all the madness and corruption that were your birthright. After much trial and error, the elemental entity known as the Swamp Thing has succeeded in harnessing the life-force of his successor into the one form with which he can co-exist - a new human soul, to be born of his love Abby (with help from the sardonic magus John Constantine). But even as the couple begin preparing for their impending domesticity, forces far beyond their intimate world are conspiring to drive them apart once more - only this time, the resulting distance may prove to be unbridgeable. Acclaimed comics creator Rick Veitch (The One, Brat Pack, The Maximortal, Greyshirt: Indigo Sunset) is joined by longtime Hellblazer author Jamie Delano and veteran Swamp Thing contributor Stephen Bissette for a mesmerizing journey through love and loss.
name: Volume 9

description:
After the stunning revelations of the last volume, Daken now knows that he is merely a pawn and that his hatred of his father, Wolverine, is based upon a lie. Now, Daken and Wolverine - father and son - unite to track down the most fearsome being Daken has ever known. But they're not the only ones looking for him. Plus, Daken battles the X-Men for possession of the deadly Muramasa Blade!

Collects Wolverine: Origins #31-36.
name: Dark Reign

description:
Wolverine may be back in S.H.I.E.L.D. custody, but at what cost? As the X-Men mourn a fallen teammate in a funeral befitting a hero, Hydra celebrates the coronation of a new leader. And the reign of terror continues, as the Hand picks off meta-humans one by one. Will Wolverine be deprogrammed in time to stop the carnage? Plus: the secret origin of the Gorgon!

Collects Wolverine #26-32.
name: Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.

description:
The world's deadliest living weapon just fell into the wrong hands. It's Wolverine vs. the Marvel Universe in the best-selling, blockbuster storyline that will have Logan shredding his way through the X-Men, Fantastic Four, S.H.I.E.L.D., and more! How does Wolverine end up fighting to destroy everything he holds dear?

Collects Wolverine #20-25.
name: Enemy Of The State

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Left shaken at ground zero after the cataclysmic events of HOUSE OF M, Logan has no choice but to soldier on, as he done so many times before - but has the burden now become too great? In his lifetime, Logan has been both a hero and a villain, a player and a pawn...but what is he now? Don't miss out on the beginning of an epic more than a century in the making.

Collects Wolverine (2003) #36-40.
name: HC/TPB

description: Wounded behind enemy lines, Captain America faces one of his greatest challenges yet—escaping a Nazi POW camp…as Steve Rogers! Brought to you by Kyle Higgins & Alec Siegel, co-creators of the fan-favorite film The League!
name: Prisoners of Duty

volume.name: Captain America Theater of War: Prisoners of Duty

description:
This volume is a reprint of all the individual issues of the five issue series by the same name. 
 

A quick look back:


Some time ago, an immensely powerful cosmic entity named "Phoenix" united itself with Jean Grey. The result: Jean was driven almost insane and her corporeal form was taken over by the Phoenix. It used their combined powers to obliterate an entire alien civilization. But the X-Men stood against her. Their powers resulted in her death. But the Phoenix lived on.... 
 

Summary:


The Shi'ar have once again reconstituted the Phoenix with a goal to destroy it completely this time. The experiment drives the Phoenix insane and it comes down to Earth to unite with Jean once again. Coming back, it finds Jean dead, and refusing to be dissuaded, it ressurrects her. Then it takes over her body. Logan is the first to make contact with her. Jean tries to fight it, but the Phoenix is too powerful for her. It has come back to claim the last missing piece of its/Jean's essence, Cyclops. 
 
Later, the X-Men are warned of the presence of the Phoenix. Beast designs an egg shaped capsule to contain the Phoenix. Scott is still trying to come to terms with Emma. Meanwhile, Storm and Nightcrawler track down a Shi'ar spaceship. Upon entering the ship and questioning the crew, they hear that the Shi'ar have come to destroy the Phoenix once and for all. But suddenly, their attention is diverted to another big energy signature, manifesting at the X-Mansion. It is of omega level. 
 
The presumed dead omega level telepath, Quentin Quire has somehow risen from the dead. His sole purpose now is to find the Phoenix and with its help, bring back to life his lost love, Sophie, a sister of the Stepford Cuckoos. He digs her corpse up from the grave and follows the Phoenix. 
 
Up in the skies, the Shi'ar detect the Phoenix and fire the event horizon weapon. Wolverine and Jean are supposedly caught in the beam's path. But later, Wolverine finds himself, resting upon Jean's lap in the Arctic Circle. Jean tells him that she should not be here. She asks Wolverine to kill her again. Wolverine complies. But the Phoenix is already taking over. It rises again and again, and Wolverine stabs Jean's body again and again. Finally, Jean takes over and buries herself in 50 feet deep ice. 
 
Elsewhere, the Shi'ar detect Quentin and prepare to kill him. Storm negotiates with them for his life and the Shi'ar accept.  
 
The X-Men reach the Arctic Circle and see Wolverine. Emma confirms that Jean is dead. But suddenly the Phoenix rises. It wants Scott's eye beams to power itself and tries to force him into doing so. But Emma stands between them. She says that to have Scott, the Phoenix must go through her. The Phoenix accepts the bait and unites with Emma. Scott forces Phoenix into the egg with himself, and Hank locks them up. Inside, Emma expresses her love for Scott, but feels the Phoenix taking over rapidly. 
 
Quentin manages to escape the Shi'ar spaceship and quickly reaches the spot where the Phoenix is trapped. After a short battle with the X-Men, he manages to crack the egg and frees the Phoenix. Then, he asks it to restore Sophie back to life. It complies and resurrects her, but Sophie does not want to live. She dies again. This saddens Quentin. The Phoenix power up.  
 
Scott calls Jean with all his heart, and she emerges from beneath the sheet of ice. She frees Emma from the Phoenix and makes it understand that what the Phoenix has come for, is not here on Earth. The X-Men express their love for Jean by uniting their minds and calling her lovingly. But that does not last long. The Shi'ar ship appears over their heads and powering up the

Event Horizon weapon

, collides with the surface in a suicidal dive. 
 
Emptiness. 
 
Scott finds Jean talking to him. She wants to see his eyes before she goes away. Scott complies and Jean bids him goodbye. 
 
The X-Men finds themselves still sitting on the spot where the Shi'ar spaceship crashed moments ago. They know that it was Jena who helped them come back from the void of the Event Horizon. Quentin frees himself of his

corporeal form.

 
Back at the X-Mansion, one of the Stepford Cuckoos makes contact with the Phoenix...

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The Phoenix is back! But where has it been reborn? Fire and pain await the X-Men. Can they handle what's to come?!  And what's up with the Stepford Cuckoos?
 
Collects X-Men: Phoenix Warsong #1-5.
name: Phoenix - Warsong

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
When last we saw Darkchylde, she had claimed the throne of Limbo as her own. And now she's determined to get her soul back, even if she has to conquer Earth in the process! Can the combined forces of the X-Men stop her rampage? They'll have to fight through every demon in Limbo to try. Plus, get the whole story of Magick's exciting return to the Marvel Universe with X-Men: Return of Magick and the X-Infernus Saga!

Collects X-Infernus #1-4, the 8-page Divided We Stand story, X-Infernus Saga, X-Men Unlimited #14, and New X-Men #37.
name: X-Infernus

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: GrimJack's quest for the Manx Cat and its secrets has led him all over the fabled multidimensional city of Cynosure-and he's in a battle-to-the-finish with the beautiful Darlin' Lil. If that's not enough, GrimJack's visit to The Sleepless Monks has him fighting for his very soul! All this effort for just one damned cat?

GrimJack's spiritual search for St. John of Knives leads John Gaunt right to the outlaw saint. In the Cynosure of the past, the origin of the Manx Cat is revealed and its powers are unleashed. GrimJack must now battle demons and agents of chaos as well as a greedy Lord Protector... but he isn't going to have to do it alone!

Gaunt's astral journey to the medieval Cynosure of his past continues. As he fights the Manx Cat, GrimJack's choices place his friends in jeopardy as he must encounter more truth than even he can handle. It's a race through time and reality-as Bob the Watchlizard disappears from sight!

"The Codebreaker" Midwestern housewife Maggie Winters is the local puzzle prodigy. But this seemingly innocuous skill is about to take a dark turn, as Maggie's "visions" manifest not as waking nightmares but as disturbing images in the mundane world around her. Plotted by the film's director, Scott Stewart, and scripted by Tom Waltz (Silent Hill: Sinner's Reward). Art by Francisco Paronzini (Dead to Rights).
name: The Code Breaker

description:
Over the course of her life, Storm has been many things: A thief. A goddess. An X-Man. A Wife. A Queen. But not until now have these roles come into conflict. When a mutant commits a mysterious murder in Wakanda, Storm takes it upon herself to investigate. And what she discovers will force her into a position where she must choose: Will she stand with the X-Men or with her husband? Writer Chris Yost (X-Force, New X-Men) and up-and-coming artist Diogenes Neves bring you the series that will change Storm forever.

Plus, relive the beginnings of the Black Panther and Storm romance with reprints of landmark issues Marvel Team-Up #100 and Black Panther #26.

Collects X-Men: Worlds Apart #1-4.
name: HC/TPB

description: Can an android dream? After waking from what appears to be just that, the android Sereda struggles with the idea that he may be more damaged than he originally thought. Still, whether it's simply his programming or a newly found free will, Sereda is hell bent on effecting the rescue of the woman whose voice brought him down into the bewildering maze of a seemingly endless necropolis. Most of the surviving planetary prospectors are willing to follow him into the labyrinth, but there are two major obstacles to the rescue mission: a horde of marauding xenomorphs, and the man who shot Sereda, who isn't about to let a damaged synthetic lead the other survivors anywhere.

Even as costumed crime fighter Empowered fights a desperate battle against a functionally invulnerable, grave-robbing supervillain inside a secret underground mausoleum for fallen superheroes, back at Emp's apartment, the alien demonlord imprisoned upon her coffee table spins a tempestuous tell-all tale of the often-struggling heroine's deepest secrets . . . The scruple-free storyteller soon reveals how all of Empowered's many frustrations at work, at home, and even in the bedroom can be conveyed strictly through the vocabulary of her extraordinarily expressive exhalations, thus making her . . . "The Wench With a Million Sighs!"
name: The Wench with a Million Sighs

description: The Secret Saturdays discover a Lost King of Africa! Plus, in The Kids Next Door, Numbah One suffers from a bad case of being dumped! And finally, Samurai Jack tries to put an end to an upcoming war!
name: The Lost King of Africa Part 1; Operation: R.E.B.O.U.D.; Parts of A Whole

description: When his people need him the most, he shall return! Lord Apocalypse is here to lead mutantkind into the future of the earth and only the strongest can survive! And just wait until you see his new Horsemen! Even we were surprised! Plus: Cable sees the signs--omens and portents -- characters gathering, moving across the board like chess pieces...can Apocalypse be resurrected? Can Cable and Deadpool stop it in time? And most surprising of all... what if one of them doesn’t want it to be stopped? Collects X-MEN #182-186 and CABLE/DEADPOOL #26-27.
name: TPB

description:
"Blackout": The Iron King wants the force-field over Sonic's home city gone, so he heads to its power source: the radioactive remains of Robotropolis! This could spell doom for our heroes - not to mention the surrounding environment! As Sonic races to the rescue, Princess Sally finally comes to a pivotal personal decision.
PLUS: "The Iron Queen:" The second half of this intriguing new villainess' thrilling origin is revealed!
name: Blackout

description: Finally putting to rest their own recent past, the X-Men embark on an all-new, all-different era of excitement! The shocking return of an enemy thought dead rocks the X-Men to their very core! Can they overcome an adversary more powerful than they imagined, or will internal strife within the team itself tear them apart first? Plus: The Brotherhood of Mutants is back with Nocturne from the Exiles, and a surprise shocker of a member! With the Xavier Institute under attack by the Brotherhood and the X-Men down for the count, the only ally the students have to help keep these villains at bay is a blind Gambit. Collects X-MEN #157-164.
name: TPB

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Werewolves, demons, monsters, vampires. All these ferocious creatures are afraid of the same thing: the beautiful Princess Hime, an awesome warrior who fights off the forces off evil with a chainsaw and a smile. Not only does she look great in a tiara, she has magical powers that allow her to raise the dead. She’s a girl on a mission, and with the help of her undead servant and a supercute robot, there’s no creature of darkness she can’t take down!
name: Have A Nice Afterlife

description:
Hiro is a Blood Warrior, which means he’s the natural prey of vampires, demons, monsters, and other creatures of the night. Even worse, he needs the help of Hime, the somewhat crazy Princess who gave him the dubious gift of immortal life at the price of eternal servitude. One thing remains clear . . . this is Princess Hime’s world, and all Hiro can do is try to survive it!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 6: Princess Alliance
  • Chapter 7: Princess Blood
  • Chapter 8: Princess Carnage
  • Chapter 9: Princess Recollections
  • Chapter 10: Panic Room Princess
  • Special Bonus
name: Immortality Bites

description:
Hiro Hiyorimi is a boy who has just moved to the Sasanaki City to meet his sister. While walking down the sidewalk, he is suddenly hit by a car. On the verge of death, he is seen by a young woman clad in gothic clothes. She then resurrects him, leaving him alive in the hospital morgue. He wakes up confused over what happened, only to encounter the woman again as she eliminates some wolf creatures. She addresses Hiro as "her servant" and introduces herself as "Hime" and explains that she is a member of the royal family of the Monster Realm.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 11: Princess Attrition
  • Chapter 12: Princess Dead Run
  • Chapter 13: Princess Monochrome
  • Chapter 14: Princess Ocean
  • Bonus Track
name: Volume 3

description:
It’s finally time for Blood Warrior Hiro to become Princess Hime’s hero. The vampires and the werewolves are clashing in a terrible feud, while the ghosts are whispering of betrayal . . . and giant insects are planning to make a meal of Hime and her friends. Only one thing’s for sure: There’s going to be even more blood-soaked mayhem and unstoppable action than ever before!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 15: Princess Connection
  • Chapter 16: Princess Sacrifice
  • Chapter 17: Princess Banishment
  • Chapter 18: Princess Underground
  • Chapter 19: Princess Coma
  • Bonus Track
name: Hiro Worship

description:
The epic battle between the royals comes to a head as Hime faces down her biggest challenge yet: a town filled with the living dead. But Hime’s blood warriors are unable to protect her. With Hiro at her side, she must save the town, kill the zombies, and find out who unleashed them. Dark secrets will be revealed, and when the culprit is put on trial, there can be only one fitting punishment: death.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 20: Night of the Princess
  • Chapter 21: Dawn of the Princess
  • Chapter 22: Day of the Princess
  • Chapter 23: Princess Duel
  • Bonus Track
name: Zombie Invasion

description:
Princess Hime is one of a kind, a monster-slaying, butt-kicking beauty. But after an alien body snatcher targets the princess, there are suddenly two Princess Himes–both gorgeous, glamorous, and totally deadly. Will her loyal blood warrior, Hiro, and her werewolf sidekick, Riza, find out who the real Princess Hime is before her evil twin destroys her?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 24: Princess Prisoner
  • Chapter 25: Princess of the Lost World
  • Chapter 26: Princess Dense Fog
  • Chapter 27: Princess Collision
  • Bonus Track
name: Evil Twin

description:
Princess Hime has devoted her life to helping others–as a butt-kicking monster-slayer. She has one very special memory: a song that she wrote for her sister. But when a wicked creature finds a way to turn that treasured memory into a curse, it’s up to Hime’s friends to find this cruel maestro–and set the princess free!

Includes special extras after the story!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 28: Princess Curse
  • Chapter 29: Princess Melody
  • Chapter 30: Princess Occult Research
  • Chapter 31: Princess Millennia
  • Chapter 32: Princess Behemoth
  • Bonus Track
name: Ghost of the Past

description:
In a world full of fear and hatred, all too often the unfortunate result is violence. Finally facing their own recent past, the X-Men come to terms with the widespread devastation of Magneto's genocidal attack on New York City -- and prepare to embark on an all-new, all-different era of excitement! Plus: When the Juggernaut tries to defend his young friend, Sammy, from an abusive father, it's the X-Man who is arrested and put on trial. Now, the former criminal must convince the world that he has truly reformed.

Collects Uncanny X-Men (1963) #435-436, 442-443, New X-Men (2000) #155-156.
name: Volume 6

description:
Most people fear them, and a few people even hunt them, thinking they are horrible monsters to be destroyed at all costs. But young Hamachi wants to be friends with them! He sees them as mischievous creatures that could coexist peacefully with humans if only given a chance.

When his grandmother dies under mysterious circumstances, Hamachi journeys into the Yokai realm. Along the way, he encounters an ogre who punishes truant children, an angry water spirit, and a talking lantern. Will Hamachi be able to find his grandmother's killer, or will he be lost forever in another world?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Yokai are Japanese spirits, and young Hamachi is fascinated by them. Now he continues his quest deep into the Yokai realm in the hopes of finding Madkap, the kappa (water spirit) he believes has killed his grandmother. Armed with nothing but a sacred rope and a lucky kappa’s foot, Hamachi has made two friends to help him on his journey: Lumi the talking lantern, and newly awakened, the umbrella that once belonged to his grandfather! (Don’t ask.)

Their first stop is the home of the legendary fox spirit the Ninetails, who promises to help in Hamachi’s quest if Hamachi can retrieve three lost items. But can Hamachi really find them, or does the Ninetails just want Hamachi to fail so he can keep the human boy as a pet?
name: Vol. 2

description: With the hostage crisis at its peak, Cynotaur the leader of Cretor, has the United Free Worlds right where he wants them; on the brink of destruction! Are the forces of the last standing army of Earth enough to end the A hostage crisis is about to begin.
name: Mahtors Origins

description: It's the triumphant return of Duck Dodgers in the 24 1/2 Century – and his trusty Cadet! There's a universal honey shortage! Can Duck Dodgers teach the Bees of the Bumble Bee Planet how to get bee-zy?
name: A Duck In Every Pot; Bugs Bunny & Beaky Buzzard In "Mama's Boid"; Planet Of The Glambots; Spick & Spanning The Galaxy

description: The Mother of all Fieldtrips. - While on a fieldtrip to the legendary Stones of Nature, Boon, Kat Nip, Klondike and Quickstep find themselves drawn into an age-old conflict between Willow, the Mother of Nature and the vile SpiderSect Empire. Reluctantly, our heroes are propelled into the fray when Mother Nature bestows to them the fabled Amulets of Nature, granting them astonishing powers. Together, they become N-Guard.
name: The Mother of all Field Trips! Part 1: When Nature Calls

description: With public patience for Middle East casualties wearing thin, the U.S. military adopts a new weapon - Zombies! Air-dropped into hot zones, the walking dead indiscriminately infect everyone. Engineered to dissolve at daybreak, they create a safe combatant-free zone. What could go wrong?
name: Operation ZMD
The Heku Trilogy - Book One - Sands Upon the Earth
The Heku Trilogy - Book Two - Community
The Heku Trilogy - Book Three - Triad

description: Following the events of issue 1, Boon and the team are faced with a graver situation... The SpiderSect Empire has discovered the potential whereabouts of the Nature's Guard. Mother Nature sends the team on a race to find the Nature's Guard before Grandsilk Weaver. Will they make it in time, or are darker threats from their past scheming against them?
name: The Mother of all Field Trips! Part 2: Some Answers and a Quest

description: Coming face to face with his brother, Boon must struggle to stay focused. But when a dire event happens and one of the N-Guard falls, Boon is faced with a realization that will change his destiny forever. Is he up to the challenge, or will he falter?
name: The Mother of all Field Trips! Part 3: The Root of All Evil

description: Conan has to battle a host of magical creatures and a legendary Guardian in order to find an ancient diamond treasure.
name: Beneath the City of Shadows

description: While at the Temple of Vajrath a priestess enlists Conan's aid in retrieving the Stolen Wheel of Life and Death.
name: The Wheel of Life and Death

description: An epic story of anger unbound! Exiled by a group of Marvel "heroes" to the savage alien planet of Sakaar, the Hulk raged, bled and conquered through the pages of last year's "Planet Hulk" epic, rising from slave to gladiator to king. Now the Hulk returns to Earth to wreak his terrible vengeance on Iron Man, Reed Richards, Dr. Strange and Black Bolt ― and anyone else who gets in the way. Stronger than ever, accompanied by his monstrous Warbound gladiator allies, and possessed by the fiercest and purest rage imaginable, the Hulk may just tear this stupid planet in half. Collecting WORLD WAR HULK #1-5.
name: World War Hulk

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Hulkbuster Armor Mk. II

object_credits.name: Iron Man Hulkbuster Armor Mk. II

description: Based on the hit virtual world with over 3 million users worldwide! When Dane and Maya return to Briarwood, Darkthorne's followers accuse them of trying to assassinate the sorceress with a deadly poison. Now the pair must survive the darkest corners of Briarwood as they search for an alchemist who can prove their innocence!
name: The Dark Throne

description:
It was the worst day in X-Men history. Now it’s the day after. The House of M is over, but the effects will be felt for the rest of their lives. How do the X-Men pick up the pieces in a world that has completely changed? Plus: Something’s amiss at the House of Xavier! A sneak attack forces the X-Men to re-evaluate just who their friends are, and to align themselves with former enemies!

Collects DECIMATION: HOUSE OF M – THE DAY AFTER and X-MEN #177-181
name: TPB

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Barack escapes from the horrific Pit of Punditry and battles his way past eldritch threats and byzantine obstacles to reach the pinnacle of the Elephant Tower whilst The Old Warrior and Red Sarah nip at his heels. At the top of the tower Boosh and his evil vizier cast down spells and aspersions.

In the small, God-fearing town of Redemption Valley, a young boy's body is found dead and mutilated. Is it a ritualistic killing? The local bad boy, Joel Flood, is arrested and put in jail. A black-garbed, "devil-worshipping" metalhead, he must be guilty...or is he? Enter attorney and super hero Matt Murdock, brought in to save the troubled teen from what looks like a witch-hunt by an outraged community desperate for justice...and the death penalty. This may be the most important case of Matt's career. A loss means justice denied and certain death for his client. Rising star David Hine (DISTRICT X) teams with critically acclaimed talent Michael Gaydos (POWERLESS, ALIAS) to tell this dark and gothic tale of prejudice, justice and punishment - inspired by the true story of "The Robin Hood Hills Murders."     
 
Reprints Daredevil: Redemption #1-6.
name: TPB

description:
Alphonse Patrillo's a rare breed: a mob boss who looked down the barrel of the Punisher's rifle and lived to tell about it. Ever since that day, he's taken pains - great pains - to stay under the Punisher's radar while he schemed his revenge. Now, Uncle Fonzie has got a plan: He's going to fight fire with fire. Who do you hire to take out a relentless psychopath like the Punisher? An even more relentless psychopath. And this guy, well, let's just say he never misses. Wall-to-wall action by the creative team behind BULLSEYE'S GREATEST HITS and SUPREME POWER: NIGHTHAWK: Daniel Way and Steve Dillon.     
 
Reprints Punisher vs. Bullseye #1-5.
name: Punisher vs. Bullseye
Il grande amore di Zio Paperone

description:
It's wall-to-wall David Lapham (Stray Bullets) as the Eisner Award-winner and indy sensation writes, pencils and inks two of Marvel's biggest icons! Daredevil and the Punisher vie for the soul of Hell's Kitchen as half the East Coast's underworld - in chaos since Wilson Fisk, the Kingpin of Crime, was deposed-scramble for a shot at the big chair. And as the city descends into chaos-as murder and intimidation become the staples of the day-Daredevil and the Punisher each seek to restore order in their own unique way. For Daredevil-who's anointed himself the city's new "Kingpin"-this means dispensing justice at the end of a billy club. But for the Punisher, justice at the end of a billy club isn't justice at all. For the Punisher, justice for these animals is at the end of a shotgun. Featuring more Marvel villains than you can shake a stick at-including Hammerhead and the return of the nefarious...Jackal!

Reprints Daredevil vs. Punisher #1-6.
name: Daredevil vs. Punisher: Means and Ends
